              "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">4. You are sitting in the Nurse's Station of the Emergency Department when the alarm goes off on the monitor for your patient in Room 15. He is here being treated for what you suspect is the flu. The monitor shows an up and down wide pattern that looks like ventricular tachycardia at a rate of greater than 300. You jump up and run into the room to find your patient sitting upright in bed talking on his cell phone. He is absently scratching at the ECG electrode on his left shoulder. You suspect the rhythm that you saw to be?</p>"
